  "texts": [
    "For sub-task 1, LoRA benefits from the multilingual training data when making predictions on 5 out of the 9 languages (DE, IT, PL, RU, and KA) and favours the monolingual English training setting for the 4 remaining languages (EN, FR, EL and ES).",
    "The difference is particularly high for Spanish, resulting in a slightly better average performance in a monolingual training scenario for subtask 1.",
    "(3) The diversity of languages in the training set has an inconsistent effect on adapter classification performance across all tasks.",
